summary: Marvel's Delightful Heroes Return In 'Marvel Rising' #1
title: Marvel's Delightful Heroes Return In 'Marvel Rising' #1
excerpt: The lovable crew of Marvel Rising is getting the gang back together for a new adventure in [...]
description:
The lovable crew of Marvel Rising is getting the gang back together for a new adventure in 2019!

The duo of Ms. Marvel and Squirrel Girl will be teaming up once more with Spider-Gwen, Inferno, America Chavez, and Quake in an all-new adventure that follows up the group’s first movie Marvel Rising: Secret Warriors. While the last time around the team was still getting together, this time they will need to be on their game as they will be taking on the powerful Morgan le Fay, or else New Jersey will be sent back to the medieval ages.

We’re pretty sure the city isn’t fond of trading their Hondas and Toyotas for carriages and horses, so here’s hoping the team can make it happen.

The new adventure will be written by Nilah Magruder (M.F.K.) and drawn by Roberto Di Salvo (Marvel Adventures Spider-Man) and will feature covers by Audrey Mok (Jose and the Pussycats).

summary: Marvel Talk
body:
Marvel Talk

Hello! I just thought of a question to ask, so as we know Disney is bringing out a streaming service app with many things on it. We know of the Loki tv series but what other Marvel series would you like to see on there?


Personally, I would love to see a continuation of the Agent Carter tv show or a new Agent Carter show but of course it still has to be Hayley Atwell.

Hello! I just thought of a question to ask, so as we know Disney is bringing out a streaming service app with many things on it. We know of the Loki tv series but what other Marvel series would you like to see on there?


Personally, I would love to see a continuation of the Agent Carter tv show or a new Agent Carter show but of course it still has to be Hayley Atwell.

summary: I feel like the sole reason Peter wasn't like "what the heck" when Tony called May attractive is because Peter's heard it so...
body:
I feel like the sole reason Peter wasn’t like “what the heck” when Tony called May attractive is because Peter’s heard it so many times already. From May’s coworkers, from people in restaurants or stores, even from Peter’s classmates on the rare occasions when she picks him up from school. People have told May and Peter so many times that she looks so good, so pretty, so hot, so good looking for her age. So when Tony says it, Peter’s just like “okay”.

I don’t know, I just find it really amusing. Way to go Aunt May.
